BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 195.60000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 1: Setting Sail) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Captain Marina and her crew of young scientists boarded the research submarine.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Today we dive to the deepest parts of the ocean!' she announced excitedly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (The submarine slipped beneath the waves into the warm, sunlit surface waters.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Sunlight sparkled through the blue water as schools of colorful fish swam past.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('This is the Sunlight Zone,' Marina explained. 'The top 200 meters of ocean.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('Most ocean life lives here because sunlight means plants can grow!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: OCEAN ZONES) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (The ocean is divided into zones based on how deep sunlight can reach:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (  Sunlight Zone \(0-200m\): Bright, warm, most life lives here.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (  Twilight Zone \(200-1000m\): Dim light, cooler, strange creatures.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (  Midnight Zone \(1000-4000m\): Total darkness, near-freezing, high pressure.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (  Abyssal Zone \(4000-6000m\): Pitch black, extreme pressure, very few animals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (  Hadal Zone \(6000m+\): The deepest trenches, barely explored by humans.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* We have explored less than 20% of the ocean floor - more of the Moon is mapped!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* The ocean holds 97% of all water on Earth and covers 71% of the surface.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Average ocean depth is about 12,100 feet \(3,688 meters\) - over 2 miles deep!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Fill a tall clear glass with water. Shine a flashlight from above - notice how light fades with depth!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why do you think most ocean life lives in the top 200 meters?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
