BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 186.0 720 Td (Chapter 3: School of Fish) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (A massive school of silver fish surrounded the submarine - thousands of them!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (They moved together as one giant shape, turning and twisting in perfect unison.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('How do they all move together without bumping into each other?' a student asked.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Each fish watches its neighbors and matches their speed and direction,' Marina explained.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Being in a school protects them - predators get confused by so many moving targets!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (A barracuda charged in, but the school split apart and reformed perfectly!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: FISH BIOLOGY) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Fish breathe underwater using gills that extract dissolved oxygen from water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Water flows in through the mouth and over the gills, where oxygen is absorbed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Fish have a lateral line - a sensory organ that detects vibrations and movement nearby.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (This lateral line helps fish swim in schools without crashing into each other!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Fish are cold-blooded - their body temperature matches the surrounding water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (There are over 35,000 known species of fish - more than all other vertebrates combined!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* The fastest fish \(sailfish\) can swim at 68 mph - faster than a car on the highway!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Some fish \(like clownfish\) change sex during their lifetime!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* The ocean sunfish \(Mola mola\) can weigh up to 5,000 pounds!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Watch a video of a fish school moving. Notice how they turn together like one organism!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why do fish swim in schools? What advantages does it give them?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
