BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 171.6 720 Td (Chapter 4: The Twilight Zone) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The submarine descended past 200 meters. The water grew darker and colder.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Welcome to the Twilight Zone,' Marina announced. 'Very little light reaches here.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Strange creatures appeared in the dim blue darkness around them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (A jellyfish drifted by, its body pulsing with an eerie blue-green glow!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Bioluminescence!' Marina exclaimed. 'It is making its own light!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (More glowing creatures appeared: fish with built-in flashlights under their eyes!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: BIOLUMINESCENCE) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Bioluminescence is the ability of living things to produce their own light!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (A chemical reaction between luciferin and oxygen creates light without heat.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (About 76% of ocean creatures in the deep sea can produce bioluminescence!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Uses: attracting prey, confusing predators, finding mates, communication.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Anglerfish have a glowing lure on their head to attract prey in total darkness.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (On land, fireflies use bioluminescence too - same basic chemistry!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Some squid squirt glowing 'ink' to confuse predators while they escape!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Bioluminescent bacteria can make dead fish glow in the dark.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* The cookiecutter shark glows to camouflage against dim light from above.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Break a glow stick in the dark. The chemical reaction inside is similar to bioluminescence!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why would making your own light be useful in total darkness?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
