BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 195.60000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 5: Giant Squid!) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (At 600 meters deep, something enormous appeared at the edge of the submarine lights.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Two huge eyes - the size of dinner plates - stared back at them from the darkness!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('A GIANT SQUID!' Marina gasped. 'We are so lucky - they are rarely seen alive!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Its tentacles stretched over 40 feet long, lined with powerful suction cups.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The massive creature glided past gracefully, then vanished into the black depths.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('For centuries, sailors thought these were mythical sea monsters!' Marina said.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: DEEP SEA ADAPTATIONS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Giant squid can grow up to 43 feet long and have the largest eyes in the animal kingdom!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Their eyes \(10 inches across!\) help them see in near-total darkness.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Deep-sea animals face extreme pressure: at 1000m, pressure is 100 times surface pressure!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Many deep creatures have flexible bodies \(no gas-filled spaces\) to withstand pressure.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Some fish have no swim bladder and have super-soft bones to survive the crushing depths.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Food is scarce in the deep, so many animals have very slow metabolisms.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Sperm whales dive 3,000+ feet to hunt giant squid - epic battles leave scars on both!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* The colossal squid \(even bigger!\) has rotating hooks on its tentacles.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Giant squid were not photographed alive until 2004 - truly mysterious creatures.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Fill a plastic bottle and squeeze it - feel the pressure? Imagine that x100 at the deep ocean!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why do giant squid have such enormous eyes? What advantage does that give them?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
