BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 171.6 720 Td (Chapter 6: The Midnight Zone) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Below 1,000 meters, there was absolutely zero sunlight. Total, complete darkness.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (The temperature dropped to near freezing. The pressure was immense.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('Nothing can survive here... can it?' a student asked nervously.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Then the submarine's lights revealed an incredible sight: a hydrothermal vent!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Superheated water \(750F!\) shot up from cracks in the ocean floor like underwater geysers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (And around it - life! Tube worms, crabs, shrimp - a whole community in total darkness!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: DEEP SEA VENTS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Hydrothermal vents are cracks where superheated water erupts from beneath the ocean floor.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Water heated by magma dissolves minerals, creating 'black smokers' \(mineral chimneys\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Extremophiles are organisms that thrive in these extreme conditions!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (These creatures get energy from chemicals \(chemosynthesis\) instead of sunlight!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (This discovery changed biology - life does not always need sunlight!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Scientists think life on Earth may have started at hydrothermal vents billions of years ago.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Giant tube worms near vents can grow 6 feet long - they have no mouth or stomach!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Vent water can reach 750F but extreme pressure keeps it from boiling.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* These vents support entire ecosystems with no sunlight at all - amazing!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Research 'extremophiles' - organisms that live in extreme conditions \(hot springs, ice, acid\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (If life can exist without sunlight on Earth, could it exist in the dark oceans of other moons?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
