BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 181.2 720 Td (Chapter 7: The Ocean Floor) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The submarine continued down to the abyssal plain - the vast, flat ocean floor.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('We are over 4,000 meters deep now,' Marina reported. 'The pressure is enormous!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Then the seafloor dropped away into an impossibly deep trench!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('The Mariana Trench!' Marina announced. 'The deepest point on Earth!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Nearly 11,000 meters \(36,000 feet\) deep - Mount Everest could fit inside with room to spare!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Even here, at the very bottom, they found signs of life. Life finds a way!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: THE OCEAN FLOOR) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (The abyssal plain covers over 50% of Earth's surface - mostly flat, muddy, and dark.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The Mariana Trench is the deepest point: 36,089 feet \(10,994m\) at Challenger Deep.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Pressure at the bottom is 1,086 times surface pressure - 8 tons per square inch!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Only 3 people have ever visited the bottom: Piccard & Walsh \(1960\), Cameron \(2012\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Mid-ocean ridges are underwater mountain chains where new ocean floor is made.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (The ocean floor is always moving due to plate tectonics - spreading and subducting.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* If you put Mt. Everest \(29,032 ft\) in the Mariana Trench, it would still be under a mile of water!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Plastic bags have been found at the bottom of the Mariana Trench. Pollution reaches everywhere.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* The deepest fish ever found lives at 27,000 feet - a snailfish.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Stack books to 29 inches \(Everest scale\). Now measure 36 inches \(Mariana Trench\). See the difference!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (How could finding plastic at the deepest point on Earth change how we think about pollution?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
