BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 152.4 720 Td (Chapter 8: Protecting Our Oceans) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (As the submarine rose back to the surface, the crew was quiet and thoughtful.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('The ocean is so incredible,' Marina said, 'and it is in danger from human activity.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (They passed floating plastic bags, tangled fishing nets, and murky polluted water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('8 million tons of plastic enter the ocean every year,' Marina said sadly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('But we can change this! Every person who cares can make a difference!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('The ocean gives us oxygen, food, and beauty. We must protect it!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: OCEAN CONSERVATION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Plastic pollution: 8 million tons of plastic enter the ocean yearly. Takes 500+ years to decompose.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Ocean acidification: CO2 dissolves in seawater, making it more acidic \(harms shells/coral\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Overfishing: taking too many fish faster than they can reproduce.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (What YOU can do: reduce single-use plastic, recycle, do beach cleanups!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Eat sustainable seafood, support marine protected areas, and spread awareness!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 72 449 Td (MORAL:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 13 Tf 72 431 Td (We must protect what we don't fully understand yet!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 342 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 401 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 381 Td (* The ocean produces over 50% of the world's oxygen \(thank you, phytoplankton!\).) Tj ET
